We need to prove that for a walk `p` from `u` to `v` in a simple graph `G`, the cardinality of the set of vertices visited by `p` (denoted `supportSet p`) is less than or equal to the cardinality of the set of edges visited by `p` (denoted `edgeSet p`) plus one. 

