   This is because `Finset.card ({u} ∪ S) = Finset.card S + 1` if `u ∉ S`, and `Finset.card ({h} ∪ E) = Finset.card E + 1` if `h ∉ E`. So we need to show `Finset.card S + 1 ≤ Finset.card E + 1 + 1`, which is `Finset.card S ≤ Finset.card E + 1`, which is the induction hypothesis.

