After simplification, we need to show that the cardinality of the support set is less than or equal to the cardinality of the edge set plus 1. Let's proceed with the induction.

```tactics
  have h1 : ∀ (p : G.Loopwalk u v), (p.support.toFinset).card ≤ (p.darts.toFinset.map dartEdge).card + 1 := by
    intro p
    induction p using Nat.strongRecOn with
    | ind h =>
      cases p with
      | nil =>
        simp
      | cons h' p =>
        simp_all [Finset.card_insert_of_not_mem, List.toMultiset_append, List.toMultiset_cons, Finset.card_map]
        <;> try { tauto }
        <;> try { 
          have h2 := h p (by simp_all)
          omega
        }
        <;> try { 
          have h2 := h (p) (by simp_all)
          have h3 := h (p) (by simp_all)
          omega
        }
      | loop p =>
        simp_all [Finset.card_insert_of_not_mem, List.toMultiset_append, List.toMultiset_cons, Finset.card_map]
        <;> try { tauto }
        <;> try { 
          have h2 := h p (by simp_all)
          omega
        }
        <;> try { 
          have h2 := h (p) (by simp_all)
          have h3 := h (p) (by simp_all)
          omega
        }
```

This completes the proof of the `vertex_edge_inequality` lemma.
